CatDescriptText: Mrs. Josephine H. Williams, self-employed, 7422 Race Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that taverns should be permitted to remain open past midnight on Saturdays?" answer reads: "I'm not in favor of taversn period. However, they should be forced to close at a certain time, and that time is on Saturday at midnight."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Josephine H. Williams, wearing trench coat and eyeglasses, standing next to man walking past wearing coat with lapels and dark hat, on Wood Street with signs inscribed "supply cameras" "RAAB...", Dimlings Candy store in background, Downtown
